From: alavont <60502972-alavont@users.noreply.replit.com>
Date: Tue, 9 Jun 2026 02:09:39 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix(review): CSR permission guards, pickup instruction empty
 state, order age indicator
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Addresses all "Must Verify" items from the code review feedback.

## CSR Permission Boundaries (API)
- POST /api/orders/:id/mark-ready: CSR role now blocked from marking orders
  assigned to another CSR (403 if assignedCsrUserId !== actor.id AND not null)
  Admins/global_admins bypass the check
- POST /api/orders/:id/fulfillment: Same ownership guard added for CSR role
- Both endpoints now write richer audit metadata:
  previousStatus, previousFulfillment, newStatus, newFulfillment, actorRole, actorId

## Pickup Instruction Validation (Frontend)
- Tracks pickupInstructionsLoaded state (false until fetch settles)
- Handles malformed JSON, non-array responses, and network failures gracefully
  (always falls back to empty array, never throws or shows undefined/null)
- When order is ready + fetch complete:
  - Instructions present → shows green panel with content
  - Instructions absent  → shows "Pickup instructions are not currently available —
    please head to the counter" (not blank, not undefined)

## Order Age Indicator (Frontend)
- Added orderAge() helper in staff.tsx: renders "2m", "14m", "1h 3m" etc.
- Shown inline on every FulfillmentCard with colour coding:
    <15m → muted (normal)
    15-30m → amber (getting old)
    ≥30m → red (urgent)
- CSRs can now instantly see which orders have been waiting longest

## Overdue Banner Fix (carried from previous task)
- Confirmed: overdue orders show amber "+MM:SS past ETA" badge in hourglass
  panel only — the green "Order is Ready" banner strictly requires
  order.status === "ready" or "delivered" (not just timer expiry)

